0.question: Which estimator performs best in the presence of noisy confounders and how does it compare to the Covariate Control (CC) estimator?
0.answer: The Entropy Balancing (EB) estimator performs best across all measures (Bias, MAE, and MSE) when confounders are noisy. While the CC estimator also performs well, it exhibits slightly higher bias and MAE compared to EB.

2.question: Which estimator has the smallest bias and best MSE performance in the case of fully observed confounders?
